530128.Title: Chokladtryffelkaka

NutritionInfo.SingularYieldUnit: Paid API plan required for nutrition.

530128.Description: Chokladkaka som jag ännu inte smakat
530128.Instructions:
1. Sätt ugnen på 175 grader
2. Smält smöret i en kastrull. Lyft kastrullen från värmen
3. Rör ner socker, kakao och vaniljsocker
4. Rör ner ett ägg i taget och till sist mjölet.
5. Häll smeten i en smord och bröad form med löstagbar kant, ca 24 cm i diameter. Grädda mitt i ugnen 20 minuter.

Kakan ska vara lite kladdig i mitten. Låt kakan kallna. Ställ den gärna kallt ca en timme innan servering. Pudra över lite florsocker. Servera ev. med vispad grädde.

530172.Title: Dry Rub for Pork Shoulder

NutritionInfo.SingularYieldUnit: Paid API plan required for nutrition.

530172.Instructions:
1.  Apply mustard and then the dry rub. Wrap tightly in saran wrap and let marinate over night.
2.  Remove from the refrigerator and let the meat come to room temperature (1-2 hours).  Add liquid marinade as necessary
3.  Smoke at 225 for 1.5 hours per pound.  Spray on mop (3/4 apple cider vinegar and 1/4 cup oil) every hour as necessary.  The meat should be at 140 after 4 hours and no need to add more wood chips at this point. Remove once the meat hits 205.
4.  Remove and let the Pork Shoulder rest for 45 minutes.  Next, use two forks to pull the pork apart.

530171.Title: dorito chicken and cheese casserole

NutritionInfo.SingularYieldUnit: Paid API plan required for nutrition.

530171.Instructions:
Preheated oven to 350 degrees. Lightly spray 9x13 pan with cooking spray. Spread half the bag of crushed doritos over bottom of the pan. Reserve one cup of cheese. Mix together remaining ingredients in a large bowl. Pour mixture over doritos. Top caserol with remaining half bag of crushed doritos and 1 cup of cheese.

Bake for 30 minutes or until bubbly. 

You can add whatever ingredients you like.

530186.Title: KFC Original Recipe Fried Chicken

NutritionInfo.SingularYieldUnit: Paid API plan required for nutrition.

530186.Instructions:
Pour the oil into the large fry pan and heat over med. heat to about 400 F. Guess if no thermometer.  Oil should not be smoking. Oil should be about ¼ to ½ inch deep.

In a small bowl, combine the egg and milk In a separate bowl, combine the remaining four dry ingredients. Cut boneless breasts into strips.  Dip each piece of chicken into the milk until fully moistened. Roll the moistened chicken in the flour mixture until completely coated. 

In groups of five or six (or more until pan is relatively full) drop the covered chicken pieces into the oil. Cook for about 15 minutes or a little more until golden brown. Repeat with the remaining chicken. Remove and place on rack or paper towels.

530192.Title: Crispy Cheddar Chicken

NutritionInfo.SingularYieldUnit: Paid API plan required for nutrition.

530192.Instructions:
Crush crackers, cut each chicken breast into 3 large pieces. Pour the milk, cheese, and cracker crumbs into 3 seperate small bowls. Toss the salt and pepper into the cracker crumbs and stir the mixture around to combine. Dip each piece of chicken into the milk and then the cheese. Press the cheese into the chicken with your fingers. THen press the cheesy coated chicken into the cracker crumbs.

SPray a 9x13 pan with cooking spray and lay the chicken inside the pan. SPrinkle the dried parsley over the chicken. Cover the pan with tin foil and bake at 400 degrees for 35 minutes. Remove the tin foil, bake for an additional 10-15 minutes m or until the edges of the chicken are golden brown and crispy.

in a medium sized sauce pan combine the cream of chicken soup, sour cream and butter with a whisk. Stir it over medium high heat until the sauce is nice and hot. Serve over chicken.

530184.Title: Flank Steak Sandwiches

NutritionInfo.SingularYieldUnit: Paid API plan required for nutrition.

530184.Instructions:
Arrange flank steak in a shallow glass baking dish or gallon plastic bag. Pour marinade over and cover. Marinate in the refrigerator 6 hours or overnight.  Turn occasionally.

Preheat grill.  Cook flank steak 5 minutes a side or until medium rare. Let sit 10 minutes before slicing.  

While meat sits, mash avocado and mix with lemon juice and salt. Stir in onions, tomatoes, and Cilantro.

To Serve: Slice sandwich rolls. Layer meat, cheese, and guacamole.

530115.Title: Teriyaki Chicken

NutritionInfo.SingularYieldUnit: Paid API plan required for nutrition.

530115.Description: Great basic Chicken Teriyaki recipe. Why use the bottled stuff when the make-it-yourself marinade is easy and so much tastier?
530115.Instructions:
Prepare marinade:

Mix soy sauce, dry sherry, vegetable oil, brown sugar and ginger.  Whisk to incorporate.  

Add to plastic ziptop bag with chicken breasts.  Gently press to remove air, and place in a bowl in the fridge for at least 2 hours, up to 6.  

Turn on grill to medium heat.  Oil grill.  Place chicken breasts on grill, and let cook for 2 minutes.  Then turn 90 degrees.  Cook for 2 more minutes and flip.  Cook for 2 more minutes.  Turn 90 degrees.  Check for doneness, remove from grill when done.  Let rest on cutting board for 2 minutes.  Slice on bias and serve atop white rice.  Sprinkle with sesame seeds and or grilled scallions to garnish.

530116.Title: Creamy Peach Pie

NutritionInfo.SingularYieldUnit: Paid API plan required for nutrition.

530116.Instructions:
1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Spray a 9x13” pan with nonstick cooking spray.
2. In a large bowl combine cake mix, butter and 1 egg; mix with fork just until crumbly. Set aside 1 ½ c. crumbs for topping.
3. Press the remaining crumbs on bottom of prepared pan; Bake 10 minutes.
4. Cut peach slices into 1” pieces; Spoon onto partially-baked crust.
5. In a large bowl, combine cream cheese, sugar, 1 egg and vanilla extract; beat with mixer until creamy. Spread over top of peaches.
6. Sprinkle with reserved crumbs; Bake 30 minutes.
7. Chill at least 30 minutes before serving
Serves 12. Store leftovers in refrigerator.
